<!-- kiem -->
This repo is a Kiem project. Its task list, decisions, and progress live in Kiem
(a synced notes store), not in this repo's files.

- Read state first: `kiem project current`, then `kiem todos` and `kiem notes`
  (add `--json` for structured output). Do not reconstruct project state from code.
- Record progress: `kiem note add "<markdown>"` for a decision/finding/plan, and
  `kiem todo check <note-id> <index>` to complete a task (re-run `kiem todos` first
  — indices are positional and the note may have changed on another device).

`kiem project add "<Name>"` onboards a new repo (writes the committed `.kiem`
marker and this pointer).
